# on changing build
# =================
# âœ… sudo docker stop $(sudo docker ps -a -q)                               --------------------------------> stop all running containers
# âœ… sudo docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml build --no-cache             --------------------------------> update images, omit the --no-cache if you want to use cache building
# âœ… sudo docker-compose down -v && sudo docker-compose up --force-recreate --------------------------------> remove and rebuild all containers, you will lose the old ones data
# âœ… sudo docker-compose up -d --force-recreate                             --------------------------------> omit the --force-recreate if you don't want to recreate all the containers
# âœ… sudo docker-compose -f docker-compose.yml logs                         --------------------------------> see the docker containers logs
# âœ… sudo docker-compose run -u <SERVICE_NAME> web bash                     --------------------------------> accessing bash shell of a service
# âœ… sudo docker-compose exec db psql --username=uniXerr --dbname=uniXerr   --------------------------------> accessing inside the db shell




